Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with spectrum sharing and pricing mechanisms, which are important topics in information theory. 
2. cs.GT (Game Theory) - The paper presents a game-theoretic model for spectrum sharing and characterizes its solution concept. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with relay-assisted cognitive radio systems, which are relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a distributed optimization algorithm for implementing the solution concept, which is related to systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the improvement of spectral efficiency, which is relevant to multimedia applications.
